We Are Looking for:A QML Developer to join our team.The Project:The scope of the project is a software to be used to setup and run high precision measuring machines in an industrial environment. It will be used to control workpieces during the production process, for manual measuring systems (parts handled by humans) and for automated systems (workpieces are handled by machines). The software has to be very reliable and fault tolerant.Some of the tasks include:• improving views for the measuring results• UI optimizations to fit to specifications• configuration for measuring a work piece• functions for time and counter based monitoring of tasks like recalibration or data export• export data in different formats (AQDEF, csv, XML, …)• template system with preconfigured components for standard measuring tasks like diameters, circular runout, axial runoutResponsibilities:• Analyze client requirements• Write quality codeRequired Competencies:Mandatory:• Good understanding of OOP concepts• Experience with design patterns• Good knowledge of QML and Qt• C++ know howNice to have:• JavaScript know how• CAD/CAE experienceWe Value:• Respect• Reliability• Strive for Excellence 





			    $(document).ready(function() { 
			    var allVideos = $('.job-video-container object, .job-video-container embed, .job-video-container iframe'); 
			    var oldWidth = allVideos.width();
			    var oldHeight =  allVideos.height();
			    var aspectRatioOS = oldHeight/oldWidth; 
			    allVideos.removeAttr('height').removeAttr('width');
			    function resizeVideoOSJS(){
				allVideos.attr('style', 'max-width: 600px; width: 100%;');
				var widthInit = allVideos.width();
				var heightInit = widthInit * aspectRatioOS;
				allVideos.attr('style', 'max-width: 600px; width: 100%; min-height: 220px; height: '+ heightInit +'px;');
				//.attr('width',  widthInit).attr('height', allVideos.height())    
			    }
			    resizeVideoOSJS();
				    window.onresize = resizeVideoOSJS; 
			    });
